race.comment: ISOLYFE (2) resumed with a 5L win in a 58 and then faded out jumping 300m and is much better than that. Presents fitter for that and he's a decent chance to bounce. SUPER SHARP (1) was comfortably accounted for in Open grade but deserved the 76 win prior. Has a handy 2kg claim and a much sharper effort is likely back to this level. VALLEY PRINCE (4) had been rock-solid placing twice before placings in a row before a 2.4L defeat up to a mile. She races forward and will be much more competitive at 1400m. THE BIG FREEZE (6) turned in a fine effort to score by 4L over this distance last start to maintain his good form of late. This is harder but he can figure in the finish. TINTERN POWER (7) will be fitter and should be around the mark.
